<HEADLINE>
<P>
YOUNG HAS 28 AS LAS VEGAS ROUTS CS LONG BEACH MEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAS VEGAS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Reserve Barry Young scored a career-high 28 points and Stacey Augmon added 18 
Monday night as 18th-ranked Nevada Las Vegas raced past Cal State Long Beach 
for a 104-74 Big West Conference victory in the Thomas and Mack Center. 
</P>
<P>
Young, a sophomore forward, made seven of 10 three-point shots and sparked a 
Las Vegas run late in the first half. He made three three-point shots and a 
layup in a seven-minute span midway through the second half. 
</P>
<P>
Young, who played 26 minutes, was 10 of 15 from the field in lead the Rebels, 
19-6 overall and 12-2 in Big West play. 
</P>
<P>
David Butler added 17 points and 11 rebounds for UNLV, which beat Temple, 
62-60, Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
John Hatten led Long Beach (12-12, 9-6) with 20 points and nine rebounds. Rudy 
Harvey had 14 points and 14 rebounds for the 49ers, who had a four-game winning 
streak ended. 
</P>
<P>
Las Vegas scored the game's first seven points and led the entire way. The 
Rebels scored 15 of the final 23 points of the first half to take a 54-33 
halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
The Rebels, who made 10 of 16 three-point shots, were ahead by 20 or more 
points throughout the second half. 
</P>
</TEXT>
