<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: COMING ATTRACTIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Shauna Snow, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former presidential hopeful Jesse Jackson is taking to the TV screen again, but 
this time as a guest on NBC's "A Different World." The episode, which will be 
taped the week of March 13 (no set air date as yet), will focus on voter 
registration. "TV is the medium to reach our youth," Jackson told USA Today, 
adding that voting is a "way for our youth to choose political participation 
over guns and violence." The Jackson episode was the idea of "A Different 
World's" producer-director Debbie Allen who says her mission is to make the 
show "about something that's important, not just who's your date this Friday." 
Shauna Snow 
</P>
</TEXT>
