<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: STAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Shauna Snow, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Legs Diamond" creator-star Peter Allen drew the first of two standing ovations 
during the final performance Sunday of the $5.3-million Broadway bomb when he 
rose from a coffin at the start of the second act and declared, "Not even 
critics can kill me." The musical about a big-time New York mobster closed less 
than two months after it opened to dismal reviews in December. Shauna Snow 
</P>
