<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOW THE CITY GREW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Hilary Iker / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Since its incorporation in 1850, the City of Los Angeles has been gobbling up 
territory through annexation to expand its borders from 28 square miles to more 
than 464. The map below shows the original city and the parcels acquired along 
the way. The table shows the city's area and population at the end of each 
decade. 
</P>
