<HEADLINE>
<P>
ARSON BLAMED IN $25,000 FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Arson is blamed for a fire that destroyed about $25,000 worth of building 
materials behind the San Diego Urban League headquarters in Southeast San Diego 
early Monday night, San Diego fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
When firefighters arrived at 5:20 p.m. at the Urban League office in the 4200 
block of Market Street, they saw a column of smoke rising from a storage area 
behind the one-story building. It took firefighters about 15 minutes to control 
the blaze, which destroyed wood and other building materials intended to be 
used for Urban League projects, fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Fire officials said late Monday night that arson had been determined to be the 
cause of the fire and that the Metro Arson Strike Team is continuing its 
investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
