<P>
A search was called off for two boys swept away by a riptide while playing in 
the surf north of Morro Rock, authorities said. Steve Dooty, 17, and 
Christopher Cabral, 13, were surfing on boogie-boards about 50 to 75 yards from 
shore Sunday when they disappeared, a U.S. Coast Guard spokesman said. The 
father of the two boys, who are believed to be stepbrothers from Dinuba, was 
watching them, but "lost sight of the boys and was unable to locate them," 
Officer Manuel Silva said. "Moments later their boogie-board washed ashore 
without the boys." 
