<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Maxwell Laboratories reported that second-quarter net income fell to $505,000 
for the second quarter ended Jan. 31, down from $661,000 the previous second 
quarter. Revenue fell to $13.7 million, down from $14.9 million a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Net income fell to $1.3 million for the six-month period ended Jan. 31, down 
from $1.5 million during the like quarter a year ago. Revenue fell to $29.3 
million, down from $31.1 million a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
Maxwell linked the drop in profit and revenue to "protests by unsuccessful 
bidders (that) delayed the start of several large programs." Maxwell's backlog 
on Jan. 31 reached an all-time high of $109 million. 
</P>
