<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY EARNINGS: PROFIT IN 4TH QUARTER DROPS 20% FOR ZENITH NATIONAL INSURANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zenith National Insurance Co., a Woodland Hills insurance company specializing 
in workers' compensation coverage, said its profit in the fourth quarter that 
ended Dec. 31 fell 20% to $9.2 million. 
</P>
<P>
Zenith's revenue in the period rose 8% to $135.3 million. The company's 
quarterly 
</P>
<P>
results included a $974,000 loss on investments, compared to a gain of $358,000 
a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
For the year, the company's profit fell 4% to $46.3 million. Revenue rose 8% to 
$508.7 million. Zenith's gains on investments fell to $836,000 in the year from 
$5 million a year earlier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
