<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY EARNINGS: NEWHALL LAND &amp; FARMING'S 4TH-QUARTER PROFIT DROPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Newhall Land &amp; Farming Co., a real estate and agriculture concern that is 
developing the community of Valencia, said its fourth-quarter profit fell 38% 
from a year earlier. Newhall's earnings for all of 1988 rose 35%, however. 
</P>
<P>
In the quarter that ended Dec. 31, 1988, Newhall's net income totaled $10.1 
million, down from $16.3 million a year earlier. Newhall's revenue inched down 
to $69.8 million from $70.5 million. 
</P>
<P>
Newhall executives were unavailable for comment, but Newhall's results often 
fluctuate depending on the pace of real estate sales. 
</P>
<P>
For all of 1988, the company's profit rose to a record $53.6 million from $39.6 
million in 1987, and its annual revenue climbed 14% to $208.2 million from 
$183.3 million. 
</P>
