<P>
WOMAN'S NUDE BODY IS FOUND STRANGLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 27-year-old Santa Ana woman whose nude body was found over the weekend along 
Lambert Road near the El Toro Marine Corps Air Station was strangled, 
authorities said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
The woman was identified Monday as Rene Cathleen Ruiz, 27, of Santa Ana, 
Sheriff's Department Lt. Bob Rivas said. 
</P>
<P>
The cause of death was determined in autopsy Monday. Rivas said that no further 
details about Ruiz's murder were released, and that the crime remains under 
investigation. 
</P>
<P>
The body was found by teen-agers about 1:30 a.m. Sunday on Lambert, north of 
Irvine Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
The unidentified teen-agers at first thought the body was a discarded store 
mannequin, but after finding it was human, notified authorities. 
</P>
