<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY EARNINGS: AUDIOTRONICS REDUCES LOSS FOR 2ND QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Audiotronics said its loss in the second quarter, which ended Dec. 31, narrowed 
to $237,000 from $301,000 a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Sales for the North Hollywood company, which designs and sells audio-visual 
equipment, rose 40% in the period from a year earlier, to $1.6 million. 
</P>
<P>
Audiotronics said it is resolving quality problems associated with shipments 
from some of its overseas suppliers. 
</P>
<P>
For the six-month period, the company lost $517,000, compared to a loss of 
$449,000 in the year-earlier period. Sales rose 7% to $2.8 million. 
</P>
