<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY EARNINGS: ELECTRONICS MAKER HCC REVERSES YEAR-AGO LOSS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HCC Industries, an Encino maker of airtight electronic components, said it 
earned $726,000 in its fiscal third quarter, compared with a year-earlier loss 
of $599,000. 
</P>
<P>
HCC recorded the profit in the quarter that ended Dec. 31 despite a dip in 
revenue to $6.5 million from $6.69 million a year earlier. However, the profit 
included a $440,000 gain from the termination of a benefits plan, and tax 
benefits totaling $258,000. 
</P>
<P>
For the first nine months of its fiscal year, HCC reported net income of 
$958,000 compared with a $1.09 million loss a year earlier. The company's 
nine-month revenue fell to $19.4 million from $22.6 million. 
</P>
