<HEADLINE>
<P>
BODY OF MAN FOUND IN MOTEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The body of a man in his early 20s was found Monday in an El Toro motel, but a 
cause of death was not immediately determined pending an autopsy today, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
A Sheriff's Department spokesman said the victim appeared to have suffered a 
head wound, but it was not known if that had caused his death. The case is 
being treated as a possible murder pending further investigation and an 
autopsy. 
</P>
<P>
Sheriff's Lt. Larry Abbott said the body was found about 9 a.m. Monday in a 
room at the Quality Suites Inn in the 23000 block of Lake Center Drive. 
</P>
<P>
Abbott said the man has been tentatively identified, but that a name would not 
be released pending positive identification and notification of next of kin. 
</P>
<P>
"Right now we're treating this as a homicide investigation, but we always treat 
situations like this as possible homicides until our investigations are 
complete," Abbott said. 
</P>
<P>
He said the Sheriff's Department had no other details of the case it could make 
public Monday night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
