<P>
U.S. ENDS ARGENTINE ARMS EMBARGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The United States ended a 12-year-old embargo on military supplies to Argentina 
by signing a $13-million sales agreement today. 
</P>
<P>
The Defense Ministry said the two countries signed an accord for the United 
States to sell Argentina spare parts for military helicopters and armored troop 
carriers. President Jimmy Carter in 1977 slapped an arms embargo on the 
then-military government because it violated human rights. 
</P>
